Sobek (also called Sebek, Sochet, Sobk, Sobki, Soknopais), and in Greek mythology called Suchos is the embodiment of the crocodile god who guards the Nile in Egyptian mythology. Since crocodiles were feared by a country that relied heavily on the Nile, the ancient Egyptians who sailed the Nile hoped that if they prayed to Sobek, the crocodile or the god of the Nile would protect them from the threat of attack by wild animals including crocodiles.
